    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter May 2nd with a focus on speed-induced efficiency, highlighted by **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (72.34) and **Junior Caminero** (67.10) as our premier starts. **Pete Crow-Armstrong** benefits from an elite +14% dynamic platoon boost against a favorable right-handed matchup, making him our highest-projected asset for stealing bases despite his lower lineup position. **Colt Keith** (66.91) also lands in the \"Strong\" tier, buoyed by a prime #3 hole projection and the benefit of a slow-delivering opposing pitcher that maximizes his stolen base equity. We are also capitalizing on **Caleb Durbin** (63.89), whose projection is heavily inflated by a +19% SP skill factor against the opposing starter, proving that even a bottom-of-the-order hitter can provide elite value when the matchup math aligns.\n\nWe are navigating a few tactical hurdles, specifically regarding **Yordan Alvarez** (53.88). While he remains a lineup staple, his score is suppressed today by a tough left-on-left matchup against an elite arm (2.97 xERA), forcing us to lean on the higher-upside platoon edges provided by **Josh Smith** (60.52) and **Hyeseong Kim** (58.26). The most difficult bench decision involved **Chase Meidroth** (47.06); he was the final cut from the active roster, narrowly edged out by the superior platoon utility of **Luke Raley**. While **Chase Meidroth** offered a respectable floor, the optimizer prioritized **Luke Raley**\u2019s dynamic matchup profile to chase the 5x5 categories. Users should monitor lineups for **Dillon Dingler**, **Gary Sanchez**, and **Trea Turner**, as all remain \"Lineup Pending.\" We are keeping **Christian Yelich** on the shelf as he continues his recovery, and we will monitor weather and final lineup confirmations to ensure no late-scratch risks compromise our total game caps.",
